<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,676,1243]" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacob Thomas &amp; Hina Mohamed" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,419,1036,1062]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="1" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brachiata">
<emphasis box="[189,419,1036,1062]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">Amazonia brachiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is compared to five other 
<taxonomicName box="[721,887,1036,1063]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="1" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[721,833,1036,1062]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">Amazonia</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
previously recorded from 
<taxonomicName box="[1191,1308,1036,1062]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="260" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rubiaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[1323,1409,1036,1062]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,1508,1532]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparative account of Amazonia species known on Rubiaceae." pageId="1" pageNumber="260">Table 1</tableCitation>
). It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sydow (1917: 145)" authorityName="Sydow" authorityPageNumber="145" authorityYear="1917" box="[281,647,1072,1099]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="1" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="polypoda">
<emphasis box="[281,418,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">A. polypoda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sydow, H. &amp; Sydow, P." box="[428,647,1072,1099]" pageId="1" pageNumber="260" pagination="165 - 268" refId="ref2688" refString="Sydow, H. &amp; Sydow, P. (1917) Beitrag zur kenntuis der Pizflora der Philippinen - Inseln. Annales Mycologici 15 (1 - 6): 165 - 268." type="journal article" year="1917">Sydow (1917: 145)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of ascospore size, but has smaller perithecia (84–134 µm 
<emphasis box="[1421,1451,1073,1098]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">vs.</emphasis>
350–450 µm). The perithecia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacob Thomas &amp; Hina Mohamed" authorityYear="2021" box="[500,640,1108,1134]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="1" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brachiata">
<emphasis box="[500,640,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">A. brachiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[694,856,1108,1134]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="1" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="psychotriae">
<emphasis box="[694,856,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">A. psychotriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar in size but the former has lobed, truncate, and long appressoria (31–41 µm 
<emphasis box="[517,548,1145,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">vs.</emphasis>
15–18.5 µm), as well as larger ascospores (39–43 
<emphasis box="[1136,1167,1145,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">vs.</emphasis>
31–37.5 µm). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacob Thomas &amp; Hina Mohamed" authorityYear="2021" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="1" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brachiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="260">Amazonia brachiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other species reported from 
<taxonomicName box="[746,863,1180,1206]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="260" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rubiaceae</taxonomicName>
in that the phialides occur both in separate mycelial branches and mixed with appressoria, while in the other species the phialides are mixed with appressoria.
</paragraph>
